<i>With his tools.</i>

756
00:47:39,235 --> 00:47:40,737
<i>The Four Walls build.</i>

757
00:47:40,862 --> 00:47:43,656
<i>A little early, but walking distance.</i>

758
00:47:54,584 --> 00:47:57,128
<i>Empty, no security.</i>

759
00:48:11,601 --> 00:48:15,063
<i>Just me, Arthur, and a little M-99.</i>

760
00:48:23,029 --> 00:48:25,782
<i>No more confessions,
no more good deeds,</i>

761
00:48:25,907 --> 00:48:28,118
<i>and no more fucking remorse.</i>

762
00:48:38,962 --> 00:48:41,172
<i>What are you doing?</i>

763
00:48:44,300 --> 00:48:46,553
<i>No, you're mine.</i>

764
00:48:51,891 --> 00:48:53,518
This isn't how you die.

765
00:48:53,643 --> 00:48:55,353
Let go!

766
00:48:56,980 --> 00:48:59,566
<i>Why keep him alive
just to kill him?</i>

767
00:49:01,609 --> 00:49:05,822
<i>But as long as it's by my hand...</i>

768
00:49:08,158 --> 00:49:10,994
Gotcha! Gotcha!

769
00:49:11,119 --> 00:49:12,328
Hold on.

770
00:49:12,454 --> 00:49:14,372
Give me your hand.

771
00:49:20,295 --> 00:49:23,047
<i>This is his solution
to remorse - suicide.</i>

772
00:49:23,214 --> 00:49:25,550
<i>That's why he could unburden himself.</i>

773
00:49:25,675 --> 00:49:27,886
<i>He knew this was next.</i>

774
00:49:28,845 --> 00:49:31,639
<i>Will it be my only solution someday?</i>

775
00:49:33,850 --> 00:49:37,979
I thought God sent you
so that I could save you.

776
00:49:38,688 --> 00:49:40,023
But God had another plan.

777
00:49:40,148 --> 00:49:41,858
<i>So did I.</i>

778
00:49:41,983 --> 00:49:43,902
He sent you to save me.

779
00:49:44,027 --> 00:49:46,446
<i>- Not exactly.</i>
- You're a hero.

780
00:49:50,909 --> 00:49:52,243
Thank you.

781
00:49:59,542 --> 00:50:01,920
<i>So much for anonymity.</i>

782
00:50:02,045 --> 00:50:04,923
<i>Arthur Mitchell,
you just got a reprieve.</i>

783
00:50:10,512 --> 00:50:13,223
So the Trinity Killer
didn't shoot you and Lundy.

784
00:50:13,348 --> 00:50:14,349
Nope.

785
00:50:14,474 --> 00:50:16,226
Someone Masuka's size shot you.

786
00:50:16,392 --> 00:50:17,310
Yep.

787
00:50:17,435 --> 00:50:19,270
- That's all we got to go on Lundy's case?
- That's it.

788
00:50:19,395 --> 00:50:23,775
Well, the upside is there's no longer a
conflict of interest for you in the Trinity case.

789
00:50:24,901 --> 00:50:26,361
You mean I can work it again?

790
00:50:26,986 --> 00:50:29,447
Thank Christ,
no more backseat driving.

791
00:50:29,572 --> 00:50:33,076
Nobody knows this case
better than you. You're taking lead.

792
00:50:33,243 --> 00:50:35,620
Motherfucker, really?

793
00:50:35,745 --> 00:50:38,164
- Well, what about Lundy's case?
- That's my case now.

794
00:50:39,082 --> 00:50:42,460
Don't worry, I'm gonna find
the shithead that shot you.

795
00:50:42,627 --> 00:50:43,711
Oh, oh, whoa...

796
00:50:43,836 --> 00:50:45,755
- Oh, are you OK?
- I'm f... I'm fine.

797
00:50:45,880 --> 00:50:46,923
You OK?

798
00:50:49,634 --> 00:50:52,762
- Well, we're done here.
- We're done.

799
00:50:52,887 --> 00:50:56,724
Morgan, update the squad
at three o'clock, please.

800
00:50:59,143 --> 00:51:01,187
Glad that didn't happen last night.

801
00:51:04,816 --> 00:51:06,067
Any regrets?

802
00:51:06,192 --> 00:51:08,945
That we didn't have breakfast together.

803
00:51:16,369 --> 00:51:18,371
At least I'll get Trinity.

804
00:51:20,164 --> 00:51:21,374
Promise.

805
00:51:29,424 --> 00:51:32,927
<i>I've killed an innocent man,
and I've saved a guilty one.</i>

806
00:51:35,138 --> 00:51:37,181
<i>I won't make that mistake again.</i>

807
00:51:38,349 --> 00:51:40,018
<i>Is that the purpose of remorse,</i>

808
00:51:40,226 --> 00:51:42,937
<i>to keep you from repeating mistakes?</i>

809
00:51:45,481 --> 00:51:48,026
You're watching me.

810
00:51:49,819 --> 00:51:51,613
I'm just concerned.

811
00:51:53,031 --> 00:51:55,658
No need. I was confused before.

812
00:51:55,783 --> 00:51:57,660
But you're not any more.

813
00:51:57,785 --> 00:52:00,663
No. Embarrassed, perhaps.

814
00:52:00,830 --> 00:52:03,291
In fact, I'd appreciate it

815
00:52:03,416 --> 00:52:07,003
if you'd think of
this weekend's events as a...

816
00:52:07,170 --> 00:52:09,255
a little accident.

817
00:52:10,256 --> 00:52:13,009
You stepped off a roof.

818
00:52:13,134 --> 00:52:15,428
It was a mistake.

819
00:52:16,846 --> 00:52:19,015
We all make them.

820
00:52:21,601 --> 00:52:23,061
Don't worry.

821
00:52:23,186 --> 00:52:25,688
Your accident
will never be spoken of by me.

822
00:52:25,855 --> 00:52:27,774
To err is human.

823
00:52:32,320 --> 00:52:35,281
Little early for a drunk-driving checkpoint.

824
00:52:37,325 --> 00:52:39,202
<i>Looks like one of Debra's DNA sweeps.</i>

825
00:52:39,327 --> 00:52:42,246
Stand over here, sir, please.

826
00:52:42,372 --> 00:52:44,332
You, sir, pull over here.

827
00:52:46,834 --> 00:52:49,379
Step on out of the car, sir, please.

828
00:52:49,504 --> 00:52:51,714
Yeah, I heard about this on the radio.

829
00:52:51,839 --> 00:52:55,551
The police are looking
for some huge serial killer.

830
00:52:57,178 --> 00:52:59,681
They have his DNA.
They're looking for a match.

831
00:53:01,974 --> 00:53:03,518
Sounds scary.

832
00:53:03,685 --> 00:53:07,188
<i>Exactly how much
do you want to live, Arthur?</i>

833
00:53:09,107 --> 00:53:13,653
I think this gentleman in the red car
has the right idea. This line is endless.

834
00:53:16,406 --> 00:53:18,324
What say we take the scenic route?

835
00:53:18,449 --> 00:53:20,785
Yeah, sure, Arthur.

836
00:53:24,163 --> 00:53:27,041
<i>A changed man at peace with himself.</i>

837
00:53:30,545 --> 00:53:33,089
<i>Maybe only monsters feel no regret.</i>

838
00:53:36,426 --> 00:53:40,263
<i>If erring is human,
then remorse must be too.</i>

839
00:53:42,849 --> 00:53:46,310
<i>Wait, does that make me human?</i>

